N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 11 ยง 130.6 - Application of section 7603

State Regulations

The provisions of section
7603
of the Insurance Law shall apply to all companies required to make contributions after September 1, 1969, except that the provisions in respect to the payment of claims shall apply only to those companies judicially determined insolvent by order entered after September 1, 1969. Notes
